Program: Outlook
Title: 08/08/2011
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00j84d9
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 9 Aug 2011
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world: today, Dr Ahmed Sewehli, the British-Libyan psychiatrist who helped set up the Misrata Psychiatry Team, to help people suffering post traumatic stress and other psychological conditions caused by the siege in the Libyan city of Misrata. Also, Mel Novak, the Hollywood bad guy - who, in real life, ministers to some of America's most downtrodden people. And, Iain Tolhurst the British man who spent twelve years building the wooden boat of his childhood dreams Show less